I know this violates the rules, please leave it up for this one coding session
text:
(DanG, thanks for all your advice. When we've delivered CancerDB I want to grab a coffee and talk about what a journey this has been).

Okay ladies and gentlemen, the cat is out of the bag. There is no turning back now. I am currently leading a team trying to radically accelerate cancer researchers so that we might have cures faster.

My undisclosed HQ location in a villa in Hawai'i was just SWOTTED by the police. I love TeamBlue, and Omar M. handled it amazingly well. Thank you Team Blue for not shooting me, and using your brains. Think for yourself people! Don't believe everything you read.

It's okay, I get it. The odds of #AcceleratingTheCures are incredibly low. Only a crazy one would think we could do it.

Tonight I need some smiles. I dedicate tonight's code session to Jared Hancock from Brockton, MA. Every time I think of you I smile. I miss you bro. I love you Courtney Brennan Maurice Hancock and the other hancocks who I don't know as well. Jared, I wish you were here man. I would have called you weeks ago. You would have believed me.

OKAY. SEND THEM. TEAM PUBLIC DOMAIN ATTACK
